{
  "texts": [
    "where S j (t) is the activity of presynaptic neuron j and h i (t) is an external input.",
    "The external input is zero except for the cue-throughout condition in Fig. 4, in which h(t) = σx for noisy MF cue x and strength σ = 0.2.",
    "The activity of neuron i at time t is probabilistically updated via the Glauber dynamics",
    "where θ is the threshold and β is inverse temperature, with higher β implying a harder threshold.",
    "Motivated by theoretical arguments, we define rescaled variables θ 0 and β"
  ]
}